Garrigatitan (meaning "garrigue giant", referring to a type of Mediterranean vegetation characterized by drought-resistant shrubs) is a genus of titanosaurian dinosaur from the late Cretaceous Period of the Grès à Reptiles Formation in France. The genus contains a single species, Garrigatitan meridionalis. The holotype specimen, belonging to a subadult animal, is estimated to be 4–6 metres (13–20 ft) long, while the adult length is estimated at around 12–16 metres (39–52 ft).